1
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:10,560
Hi.

2
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:13,760
My name is Coco, I'm a new trainee at Glamorous Airline.

3
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,000
Let's start with the first job.

4
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,400
What alcoholic drinks have you got?

5
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:17,720
You can't drink that.

6
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,200
Why not?

7
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,920
you’re pregnant and still want alcohol...

8
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:21,920
I'm just fat!

9
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:24,280
My name is Nampetch.

10
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:28,240
HR told me to sit and wait here for the interview.

11
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:29,400
Hello, I have a package delivery.

12
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,480
Or maybe someone casted a black spell on us again?

13
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,800
Three, two, one...

14
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,760
How did you end up in my body, Chai?

15
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:37,640
I'm not Chaba!

16
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,320
I'm not leaving this body!

17
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:40,320
Don't tell me that Chaba is possessed!

18
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:47,200
Chai...

19
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:51,200
I would like to take a vacation for fifteen days.

20
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,000
I will take puppy Bubu to a special training course.

21
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:00,600
That important? Fifteen days enough for that?

22
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:04,600
I think you should just quit the job instead.

23
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,000
What? I can't even ask for this?

24
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Work is tiring, salary is low. Just wait, one day...

25
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,680
Stop whining already.

26
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,240
Look at those three...

27
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,480
All-New, Sky, Kreetha...

28
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,560
They're babysitting the new trainee right now,

29
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,800
and not one complaint.

30
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,800
Fine, fine, fine.

31
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:40,400
Hello, my name is Nampetch.

32
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:45,200
HR told me to sit and wait here for the interview.

33
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,800
So, Nampetch, what position are you applying for?

34
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:05,040
Nampetch, why do you want to work here?

35
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,480
Because the flight attendants are hot, right?

36
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,560
Hey, isn't she acting weird?

37
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,160
You think they'll even hire her?

38
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,400
I think with that vibe she's definitely iodine-deficient.

39
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,360
Aahhh!

40
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,000
Hairy!

41
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,720
Harry? Harry?

42
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,720
Which Harry?

43
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:33,760
Hairy! Hairy!

44
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,480
Chai, it's Chai, not Harry.

45
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:35,960
It's Chai.

46
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,280
Hairy!

47
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:39,000
Nampetch is scared of anything hairy...

48
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
It's hairy! Nampetch is scared!

49
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,200
If that scares you, there's more hairy stuff coming.

50
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,200
Hairy, Nampetch is scared of hairy stuff.

51
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,560
What the heck?

52
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,000
What? You're scaring me too!

53
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,240
That face!

54
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,440
What about my face?

55
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,440
Fake Botox face!

56
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,960
Nampetch is scared!

57
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,240
Nampetch is scared of Botox!

58
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,240
Nampetch is scared of stiffness!

59
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,520
What now? And today the A/C is broken too, it's so hot.

60
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,480
Ahh, sweat!

61
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,600
Look at those sodium beads!

62
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,240
Nampetch is scared of sweat and wetness!

63
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,960
Nampetch doesn't like it!

64
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:20,240
Nampetch is scared, Nampetch is scared!

65
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,240
You, psycho.

66
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,480
Scared all by yourself.

67
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,280
Scared of literally everything.

68
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:26,520
How did you even manage to leave the house?

69
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,160
All-New, what time is it now?

70
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:42,880
Huh? That new trainee still hasn't shown up?

71
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,040
I'll definitely fail her evaluation.

72
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,680
Hey, isn't that our airline's flight attendant?

73
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,880
So confident.

74
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,320
She thinks she's so pretty.

75
00:04:56,840 --> 00:05:00,840
Whoa, Sky, she is walking right towards us...or maybe...

76
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,440
Hi.

77
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,640
Hi.

78
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:10,600
I'm Coco, the new trainee of Glamorous Airline.

79
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:14,400
You must be Kreetha, right?

80
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,880
And you must be All-New.

81
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:24,600
And this must be Sky, Coco's mentor?

82
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:28,920
That's right, I'm Sky.

83
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:34,320
The number one flight attendant of Glamorous Airline.

84
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:37,680
Sky, so beautiful.

85
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,680
Look at your hair!

86
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:44,040
The highlight job is so detailed, like strand by strand!

87
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,000
That's gray hair.

88
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,000
Oops! Sorry, I thought it was a highlight.

89
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:54,280
So, are you ready?
What would you like me to do today?

90
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,400
You're ready, Coco?

91
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,800
I'm ready.

92
00:05:58,840 --> 00:05:59,840
Great, then.

93
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,440
Let’s get started.

94
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,760
We're working in economy class today.

95
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:07,280
Oh! Economy class!

96
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:11,280
So exotic!
I have only flown business class.

97
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:16,480
I never even knew there were seats behind the plane.

98
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:23,000
Wow, Coco, you are as exotic a trainee to us
as economy is to you.

99
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,320
Alright, let’s start with the first task.

100
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,840
Checking boarding passes.

101
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,160
Okay, let’s go.

102
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,160
Please.

103
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,360
We’ll let the trainee check first.

104
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,160
Passenger’s here, check the boarding pass.

105
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:51,240
Did you steal someone’s card?
Who is this in the picture?

106
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:53,240
That’s me!
It’s my card!

107
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,360
Oh, I see now.

108
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,880
That was before you discovered Botox, right?

109
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:01,880
Now you’ve pumped so much you look like another person.

110
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:07,960
Why are you letting your staff talk to passengers like this?

111
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:14,280
Coco! Uh, Coco dear, step aside.
I’ll do it.

112
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:16,400
Why? Did I do badly?

113
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,520
Really badly.

114
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,760
Uh, sorry, the voices in my head were a bit loud.
I’ll do it myself.

115
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,440
All done.

116
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,680
But she really has had a lot of work done.

117
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:37,640
How could you talk to a passenger like that?
You!

118
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:41,040
Didn’t you see?
She really has had a lot of work done.

119
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,320
Even more than me.

120
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,560
I’m scared. Nampetch is scared.

121
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,760
Hello, I have a package delivery.

122
00:07:56,760 --> 00:08:00,600
Thank you.
Wait, whose is this? Oh…

123
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,720
Where’s he rushing off to?
We didn’t even ask who it’s for.

124
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:07,720
Is it for Chai?
Or for you, Tid-Gift?

125
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:11,320
Or maybe for Nampetch?

126
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,640
Nampetch is scared. Scared of corners.

127
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,640
Oh wow, scared of corners too.

128
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,920
Why does this box look so familiar?

129
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,200
Is this a Manjujii box?

130
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,720
Hey, what if there’s a hunter inside?

131
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,480
Nampetch is scared.

132
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:32,920
Wait, could someone be casting spells on us again?

133
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,960
Oh no, please not that.

134
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,960
Cursing, cursing...

135
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:38,680
Nampetch is scared.

136
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,840
Then we have to open it quick.

137
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,240
If it is, we can call Shaman Akkee to deal with it.

138
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:45,040
Nampetch is scared.
Scared of Akkee. Isn't that fire hazard?

139
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,040
Nampetch is scared.

140
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:51,440
If I open it and it’s cursed, the curse will hit me alone.

141
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,440
Chai, come.

142
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,240
Fine, but Chaba has to do it too.

143
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,800
Alright, then Nampetch has to do it as well.

144
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:01,120
Nampetch is scared.

145
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:03,320
Show some spirit, HR is watching.

146
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,320
Let’s open it together.

147
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,520
Three, two, one.

148
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:26,680
Tid-Gift!

149
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,040
What?

150
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,880
Tid-Gift!

151
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,360
Yeah, it’s me.

152
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,520
Wait, why are you in my body, Chai?

153
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:40,080
Tid-Gift!

154
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,080
How did you get inside my body?

155
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:47,360
Stop, don’t grab my boobs! No, no!

156
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,480
Nampetch!

157
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,720
Don’t point at Nampetch, please.
Nampetch is scared.

158
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:55,640
Nampetch is scared, scared!

159
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:00,080
Sodium...it's sodium.

160
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,080
Nampetch is scared.

161
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:06,720
Don’t tell me you two also...

162
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,720
Nampetch is scared.
Nampetch wants to go home.

163
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:14,840
Mom told me not to come out.

164
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,640
Nampetch wants to go home already.
Nampetch is scared, scared!

165
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,840
Nampetch is scared...scared of loud people.

166
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:26,960
What are we waiting for?

167
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:30,360
Normally, I fly business class.
I never have to wait like this.

168
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:33,360
Just like me.
I never wait for anyone either.

169
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:36,400
One time the plane already flew all the way to Prague.

170
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,120
It circled back just to pick me up.

171
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,520
Prague in Czech?

172
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:41,520
Prague-Chong.

173
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:45,640
Wow, so elegant. It's high-class.

174
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:51,000
Since my birthday, I never even knew things like this existed.

175
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,240
Are you being sarcastic right now?

176
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:54,200
No, no, no, no.

177
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:56,200
I really mean it. It’s true.

178
00:10:57,920 --> 00:11:00,920
It’s starting. No one’s giving in.

179
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:01,920
What do they call this again?

180
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,360
If you’re flawless, I’m flawless.

181
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:07,680
By the way, I envy you, Sky.

182
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:11,680
Being a flight attendant,
you get to dress beautifully every day...

183
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:17,240
And being a flight attendant,
you must fly often, right?

184
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,320
You must travel a lot.

185
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:22,320
Yes, I fly European routes only.

186
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,680
I love Europe.

187
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,600
Normally when I’m bored,

188
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:31,600
I just take a private jet to see the northern lights at the South Pole.

189
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:35,680
Or play with penguins...they're so cute.

190
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:39,960
Damn. Coco gets one point, Sky gets zero.

191
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:44,640
So where do you usually go eat?

192
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:46,960
We just eat at the fancy mall near our place.

193
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,400
Which one? I want to go too.

194
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,320
The Old Siam.

195
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:56,320
Wow, so vintage.
It's perfect for your face.

196
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,480
Man, I feel sorry for Sky.

197
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:04,480
Yeah, bragging her way into digging her own grave.

198
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:08,680
And after work, how do you get home?

199
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:10,720
Someone comes to pick me up.

200
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:15,880
Uh, Sky, didn’t I see you take the bus?

201
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,880
Wow!

202
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:25,880
Sky, you are so brave because buses are so scary and dangerous.

203
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:32,280
But if you have the heart to sit on one, I truly respect you.

204
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,280
Brave, my ass.

205
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:43,040
Don’t you wonder how we even swapped bodies?

206
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:46,400
As far as I remember, we opened the box together, right?

207
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,400
Yeah, it must be that box.

208
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:53,480
Nampetch is scared.
Nampetch is scared of rectangles.

209
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:56,280
Can you just call it a box?
Nampetch is so scared.

210
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:59,480
Oh please, stop being scared for a second, girl.

211
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,480
And now that you’re in my body,
you look ten times faker.

212
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,760
But I think if it really is this box,

213
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:09,760
we just need to try opening and closing it again, right?

214
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:13,160
Wow, Tid-Gift, so clever, huh?

215
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,160
Chai!

216
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:16,280
Come on, let’s try.

217
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,760
Pray hard.

218
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:25,480
Three, two, one.

219
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,480
No, I don’t want this.

220
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,680
I don’t want to be in Chai’s body. No!

221
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,480
This chest is too heavy.
I can’t get used to it.

222
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:42,280
Oh Tid-Gift, I actually want to be in your body so bad...huh?

223
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:43,280
Like a little pony.

224
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:46,320
Nampetch doesn’t want to stay in this round-shaped body.

225
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:47,320
Nampetch wants to go back to her own body.

226
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:50,320
Nampetch is scared.
Nampetch is scared of circles.

227
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,800
Oh, this is the body I’ve been dreaming of.

228
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:56,040
34–25–38.

229
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,720
I’ll use this body to the fullest.

230
00:13:57,720 --> 00:14:01,040
No, you can’t.
Take your round-shaped body back.

231
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,040
Nampetch doesn’t want this body.

232
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:12,000
Fine. In the meantime,
figure something out yourselves. I’m going to pee.

233
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:15,400
No, Chai, don’t you dare!
I won’t let you see my stuff!

234
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:19,440
Stop pretending.
I don’t want to pee but it's your body that's calling.

235
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:22,880
No, no, no! Don’t go!
Sit down right here! No!

236
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:27,640
So does anyone have a good idea how we can swap back?

237
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,000
I saw it in a movie once.

238
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:33,000
They ran into each other and swapped bodies.
Want to try?

239
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:36,920
Nampetch is scared of pain.
Nampetch doesn’t want that.

240
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,920
Nampetch isn’t strong enough for that.

241
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,920
Or do you want to stay in this round-shaped body forever?

242
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:47,280
No! Nampetch gives up.
Nampetch will run into someone.

243
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,960
Chaba, what about you?

244
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:50,960
Fine, fine.

245
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,120
But are we in a hurry?
I want to walk around Siam first.

246
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:58,120
No! Nampetch has never walked in Siam.
Nampetch only walks in the fresh market.

247
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,680
Nampetch doesn’t want this.
Nampetch is scared.

248
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:01,680
Will Siam be dangerous for Nampetch?

249
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,000
No going to Siam?

250
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:04,960
No!

251
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:05,960
But going to the market is okay?

252
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Yes!

253
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,440
Yeah...that’s kind of weird, isn’t it?

254
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:11,240
Alright then, ready?

255
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:16,320
Three, two, one.

256
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,400
Yay! Finally we’re back in our own bodies!

257
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:31,320
Don’t tell me I really got my body back?

258
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:34,320
Not yet. I was just entertaining you all.

259
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,640
So what should we do now?

260
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,120
Nampetch is scared, so scared.

261
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,000
Nampetch wants her body back.

262
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:45,600
I don’t think something this small can swap us back.

263
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,600
It has to be stronger.

264
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:48,800
Like what, Tid-Gift?

265
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,080
Electric shock.

266
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,680
Nampetch is scared, so scared!

267
00:15:57,680 --> 00:16:00,680
Electricity Authority...
Nampetch is scared of electricity. It’s dangerous!

268
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,480
Could I have one grape juice, please?

269
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,720
Of course.

270
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,720
Coco, dear, could you grab a grape juice, please?

271
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:13,880
One moment, please.

272
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,640
Coco, dear, grab a grape juice, please.

273
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:23,760
One moment, please.

274
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,440
Coco!

275
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,080
What is it, Sky?

276
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,640
I’m checking my eyelashes right now.

277
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:36,240
If you talk so loud, my lashes will fly away!

278
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:38,480
Move.

279
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:52,320
And when beautiful Coco finishes checking her lashes,

280
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,200
please go serve the passengers in the front row for me.

281
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,600
Yes.

282
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,680
Ouch, so heavy.

283
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:06,920
Hi.

284
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,440
What would you like to drink?

285
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:12,640
What kind of alcohol do you have?
Recommend me something.

286
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:16,520
We have quite a lot.
But you…

287
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:20,080
Oh, no. You can’t drink alcohol...

288
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:22,920
Huh? Why not?

289
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:26,920
What is going on?
Why can’t I order? What’s wrong?

290
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,960
Well, because...

291
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:32,840
you’re pregnant and still want alcohol.
That’s not okay.

292
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:34,840
It’s not good for the baby, you know?

293
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,480
What the hell, you're crazy!

294
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:42,520
I’m just fat. I’m not pregnant.

295
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:47,120
And besides, I’m a man.
How the hell would I be pregnant?

296
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:51,320
Oh my God!
Why didn’t you say from the start it was just fashion?

297
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:54,800
Then I could recommend you my personal trainer.

298
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:57,160
What? Did you just call me fat?

299
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:57,720
Uh, no no.

300
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,880
What is going on here?

301
00:17:58,880 --> 00:17:59,520
Uh, no no.

302
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,840
Why are you insulting me out of nowhere?

303
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:03,800
Dear slim-waist passenger, no, it’s not like that at all.

304
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:08,800
This isn’t called fat.
This is called squishy-cute.

305
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,000
Yes.

306
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:11,680
Really?

307
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,680
Yes, yes. Just perfect.

308
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,640
Of course, handsome passenger.

309
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:18,200
Are you feeling sore anywhere?

310
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,440
We’ll take care of you.

311
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:21,440
Oh, that’s good. My legs, my legs...

312
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,800
Coco, go serve the others first. Go.

313
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:31,720
Dear passenger,

314
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:33,640
if you’d like to eat anything, just tell me.

315
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:35,640
We have it all.

316
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,840
And if he wants lobster,

317
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:41,160
or caviar,

318
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,440
or mineral water from the Alps,

319
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,440
would we have that?

320
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,680
Go serve!

321
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,880
Excuse me, excuse me.
Can I order food?

322
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,440
Yes, what would you like?

323
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,920
Hmm, coconut curry, please.

324
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,920
What? What is coconut curry?

325
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:04,360
I grew up with truffle soup and things like that.

326
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,360
We don’t have that on this plane.

327
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:07,920
What would you like again?

328
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:09,680
Coconut curry, please.

329
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,680
Oh, coconut curry, we do have!
Yes, yes!

330
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:17,080
From our airline, it’s the special coconut curry from Mae Jim’s pot.

331
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:21,200
Brand new, fresh and hot from Mae Jim’s kitchen.

332
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:23,080
Fragrant, delicious, steaming.

333
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:27,080
This coconut milk is squeezed from
real hand-grated coconuts, one hundred percent pure.

334
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,680
Please enjoy your meal.

335
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,600
Go quickly!

336
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:45,600
Oh god, come on.

337
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:48,360
Should we shock now?

338
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,240
Where did you even get this from, Chai?

339
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,920
From the car, obviously.

340
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,200
That’s my car key!

341
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,560
Well, my car key is with you, isn’t it?

342
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:57,960
Chai!

343
00:19:57,960 --> 00:19:59,960
Can you stop complaining already?
So what’s next?

344
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:03,560
From what I saw in the movie,

345
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:06,920
to swap back we need an electric shock.

346
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:09,920
Tid-Gift, are you serious?
We could die!

347
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:13,240
Of course! So, should we do it?

348
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,240
Nampetch is scared.

349
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:18,040
Nampetch doesn’t want electric shock.
Nampetch is scared.

350
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:18,960
What now?

351
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,960
Nampetch is scared of plus and minus poles.
They’re dangerous!

352
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:26,480
If you don’t do it, I swear I’ll strangle you.

353
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,880
Don’t strangle Nampetch!
Nampetch is scared!

354
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,480
Nampetch will do it!
Nampetch will do it!

355
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:34,960
Choking already?
Your body’s right here!

356
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:36,960
I'm not scared.

357
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,320
You're okay now?

358
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,320
Yes.

359
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,400
Everyone, come help.

360
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,960
Chai, do you think this could actually kill us?

361
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:50,960
If I die, I want to die in my own body.

362
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:53,440
Nampetch is scared.

363
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:57,040
Seriously, were you born in a lab or something?
You’re scared of everything.

364
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:01,400
Not everyone is as strong as you, Chaba. Miss fat...

365
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:07,120
Alright, everyone ready?

366
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,120
Plug it in!

367
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,400
Three.

368
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,600
Two.

369
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:11,880
One.

370
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:30,520
And the next thing we will learn is cleanliness.

371
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:32,160
I am already clean.

372
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:36,160
I bathe in a jacuzzi and do rose aroma spa every day.

373
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,960
Good, then.

374
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:39,760
Go collect the trash.

375
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:42,360
Oh, disgusting!

376
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,440
No, I will not do it.

377
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:50,640
You must. If you don’t, you won’t pass the training.

378
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,480
Cheap plastic!

379
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,320
Disgusting!

380
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:07,160
Do you think Coco can handle this?

381
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:10,760
It smells so bad. I can’t take it.
I’m going to faint.

382
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:13,760
Yeah, true. Sky is brutal.

383
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,720
That Coco, she finally stopped complaining.

384
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,400
So, Coco, how is it now? Getting used to it?

385
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:31,080
I told you, to be a good flight attendant,
you must be ready to do every duty.

386
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:33,080
That’s how I’ve been here this long.

387
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:40,720
Wait! All-New, Kreetha, what are you doing here?

388
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:43,880
Don’t you have work to do?
Stop being nosy!

389
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,480
Sorry, Sky.

390
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:50,480
It’s just because of my beauty.
That’s why they had to come help.

391
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:53,800
Right.

392
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:59,800
This girl is too much.
She’ll get a piece of me later.

393
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:07,680
Uh, Coco, dear.

394
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:11,680
I think collecting trash might not be right for you.

395
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:15,840
Because you’re so beautiful, so well-bred, so refined.

396
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:20,520
I think you should scrub the toilet instead.

397
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,240
No way!

398
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:24,600
No way, Sky!

399
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:27,000
I cannot scrub toilets.

400
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:31,000
How could my soft, delicate hands scrub who-knows-what?
Impossible!

401
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:35,560
I’ll just go home and have my mother build
a brand-new bathroom on top of the old one.

402
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,560
But I will never scrub toilets!

403
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:43,560
That’s fine. If you won’t scrub,

404
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:47,600
then please go back to selling artichokes...

405
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:51,400
at the Sunday Market in suburban London.

406
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,400
You will never pass this training.

407
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,480
Hand me the alcohol spray, please.

408
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,000
Thank you, thank you.

409
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:33,720
By now Coco’s probably scrubbing toilets
until her hands are torn apart.

410
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:37,720
Lucky for her that my best friend
Chaba isn’t on this flight.

411
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:42,120
Otherwise, she’d be in way bigger trouble.

412
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:47,200
I’m finished, Sky.

413
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:47,840
Finished?

414
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:48,840
Yes, I’m finished.

415
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:54,840
This is cleaner than my bedroom.

416
00:24:56,880 --> 00:25:00,320
Good job, Kreetha, All-New.

417
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:04,240
Sky said it’s cleaner than the place she lays her head.

418
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,240
I’m so happy!

419
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:12,440
All-New, Kreetha.

420
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:14,480
You again?

421
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:17,280
She didn’t know how to do it.

422
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:25,280
Here, this is for cleaning the toilet.

423
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,000
This, for your pretty face.

424
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:36,400
And this leftover, just take it.

425
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:39,440
Feels heavy in my hands.

426
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:44,880
If you’ve got anything else to hire me for,
hire me for everything. I don’t mind at all.

427
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,120
Kreetha!

428
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:48,960
Sky, are you alright?

429
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,800
Your face looks like a toilet scrubber.

430
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,520
Coco!

431
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:01,760
Why did you even help her?

432
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,000
Tid-Gift!

433
00:26:17,120 --> 00:26:18,120
Chai!

434
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,120
So that means it worked.

435
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:30,440
What are you all so happy about?

436
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:32,440
Because my method worked, Chaba.

437
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:33,440
I got my body back.

438
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:35,840
You…

439
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:37,360
Tid-Gift is back, baby!

440
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:40,520
Your fat friend is still in that body, though.

441
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:43,720
I’m still here, bitches.

442
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:47,040
Wait, why didn’t you two swap back?

443
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:48,040
Maybe it only works for one pair at a time.

444
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:52,600
Tid-Gift, go shock them again.

445
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:53,600
No need.

446
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,200
Heaven has granted me this body.

447
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,760
Shouldn’t you ask Nampetch first?

448
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:05,200
Nampetch wants her skinny matchstick body back.

449
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:07,440
Nampetch doesn’t want to stay in this round body anymore.

450
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:11,440
No. I’ll use your body to the fullest.

451
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:15,360
No! What are you going to do?

452
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:17,960
Let me borrow it for some fun.

453
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:21,720
No! Nampetch is scared of fun.
Nampetch doesn’t want it.

454
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,720
Catch me if you can.

455
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:35,120
Why is Nampetch so tired in this body?

456
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:39,680
And why do I feel so light and agile in this one?

457
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,800
Follow me, quick!

458
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,320
Where are you going?
Give the body back!

459
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:47,000
Take the battery back too, Tid-Gift.

460
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,520
How can I lift it? I’m a woman.

461
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:51,120
But you just carried it earlier.

462
00:27:51,120 --> 00:27:54,080
That was you carrying it, in my body.

463
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,080
So you better carry it back.

464
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:03,120
Hurry up so we can go check on those two. Go!

465
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:16,480
Why does it feel easier to lift when I’m in your body?

466
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:17,480
Damn, you’re sturdy.

467
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,600
Well, that’s because you’ve been on too many steroids.

468
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:30,520
Yes, okay.

469
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,640
Coco.

470
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:34,960
Coco, dear.

471
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:39,680
Coco.

472
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:44,720
Coco.

473
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,200
Coco!

474
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,040
Did you two see Coco?

475
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,880
We’re aiming at the same person...

476
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,640
Coco, what are you doing here?

477
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:13,760
Oh, I’m providing a service to a passenger, Sky.

478
00:29:13,760 --> 00:29:16,720
But since you’re here, I would like two glasses of champagne,

479
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:17,800
one lamb steak,

480
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:19,800
and one avocado salad, please.

481
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:23,960
All-New, Kreetha, can you give me a massage?

482
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:26,960
Today I’m like, very, very, very tried.

483
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:31,360
Secret code: want to watch Mor Lam show...

484
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:35,680
To the curtain! To the curtain!

485
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:37,880
Damn, so many stupid people...

486
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:45,880
All-New, call HR.

487
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,720
Who the hell did they send us?

488
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:49,720
Have this trainee back right now.

489
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,040
It's connected.

490
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:59,400
Hello, HR?

491
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:04,480
What kind of trainee did you send us?
It's about Coco.

492
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:05,480
She's so dumb, so very dumb.

493
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:07,080
Yeah, Coco.

494
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,360
Coco, the buffalo.

495
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:13,800
What?
The trainee was in an accident,

496
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:15,400
postponed till next month?

497
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,680
Then, who the hell is this?

498
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:29,920
All-New, go get her ID card.

499
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:32,280
I’ll search who she really is.

500
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,280
Yes.

501
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:39,680
Coco...

502
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:40,440
Yes?

503
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,800
Could I see your ID card, please?

504
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:44,800
Oh! PDPA! Why do you need it?

505
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,800
Just to do some research.
In case you’d like to change your surname.

506
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,880
To use mine.

507
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:54,880
Oh my god! I'm so shy right now.

508
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:59,560
Alright, then.
So many choices, I can’t decide.

509
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:07,600
Check it.

510
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:17,560
Oh my god! Coco is a psychiatric patient.
The hospital is looking for her.

511
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:30,760
I knew it. Acting weird, talking weird,
weird from the very start till now.

512
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:34,880
Weird like this... she must face me!

513
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,080
That roasted Coco-nuts!

514
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:43,200
So, how many kids are we gonna have?

515
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:45,920
Coco, dear.

516
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:50,440
Since this flight is your last flight as a trainee...

